<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Uhl</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-05"><hi rend="italic">June 5,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Proposed bill extends and modifies North Pacific sealing act, 1893,
                            expiring July, 1895, carrying into effect convention between Great
                            Britain and Russia, but is not intended to affect or impair Bering Sea
                            award act, 1894.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bayard</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>